snippet.textDisplay: So my buddy literally just had this kit put in his truck last year. The only company that's offering a decent programmer is tyrant tuning and they release new tunes monthly. Everything from 60hp towing and economy tunes, to 250+ Performance tuning. They also offer different tunes depending what you want the exhaust to sound like at idle. The one the boys have on is called HISS. It keeps the turbo vanes in the stock configuration, and also aids in cold start warm up time. But they also make all the same power level tunes in a RUMBLE that sound alot better in my opinion. And also the 250+hp tune recommends a lift pump even though the stock one is rated to approximately 750hp. 👍 I also have a DPF and EGR solution kit on my truck but I have a 2012

snippet.textDisplay:
Okay guys... umm, an FYI - in Canada we also eat burgers, not “deer burgers”! LMAO. I’m sure some people do, but I’d say most of Canada prefers a good ole hamburger. We also have Five Guys here, which I would agree with you about being one of the best burgers around. They sure know how to fill you up and actually overload you with fries! Someone posted nothing beats a grilled burger, and have to agree, making your own, firing up the outdoor BBQ and doing it yourself... ya, nothing beats that, especially in cottage country! 😁

Burgers Priest (yes, that’s actually their name) has to come in a tie with Five Guys, Webber’s (Muskoka Ontario) is always awesome.... if I don’t include my own BBQ’d burgers, then it’s very hard to pick a “best”, so we’ll stick with your Five Guys choice and leave it there. (But please... lol, no more “deer burger” comments, and we don’t drive dog sleds or live in igloos either!) 🤣🤣

Keep up the AWESOME work guys, you’re knocking it out of the park.
